It is often useful to perform a find&replace preserving the case of the matched occurrences. Example:

```cpp
#ifndef INCLUDED_FOO
#define INCLUDED_FOO

struct Foo
{
};

inline constexpr Foo foo{};
```

Let's say I want to rename "foo" to "bar". I currently have to perform 3 different find&replaces:

* "FOO" -> "BAR"

* "Foo" -> "Bar"

* "foo" -> "bar"

Ideally, I would like to perform a single case-preserving find&replace that performs all the transformations written above.

Example:

* Execute "case-preserving find&replace from 'foo' to 'bar'".

* Result: 

    ```cpp
    #ifndef INCLUDED_BAR
    #define INCLUDED_BAR

    struct Bar
    {
    };

    inline constexpr Bar bar{};
    ```
